1 7. "Domestic distillery" means a distillery that produces twenty - five thousand gallons or
2 less of distilled spirits per year.
3 8. "In bulk" means in containers having a capacity not less than one-sixth barrel for use
4 for the sale of malt beverages at retail.
5 8.9. "Licensed alcohol carrier" means a person licensed to transport or deliver alcoholic
6 beverages to a consumer without first having the alcoholic beverage delivered through
7 a wholesaler licensed in this state.
8 9.10. "Licensed logistics shipper" means a person that provides fulfillment house services,
9 including warehousing, packaging, distribution, order processing, or shipment of
10 alcoholic beverages on behalf of a licensed direct shipper and by way of a licensed
11 alcohol carrier.
12 10.11. "Licensed premises" means the premises on which beer, liquor, or alcoholic beverages
13 are normally sold or dispensed and must be delineated by diagram or blueprint which
14 must be included with the license application or the license renewal application.
15 11.12. "Liquor" means any alcoholic beverage except beer.
16 12.13. "Local governing body" means the governing entity of a city, county, or federally
17 recognized Indian tribe in this state.
18 13.14. "Local license" means a city, county, or tribal retail alcoholic beverage license issued
19 by the appropriate local governing body.
20 15. "Manufacturing distillery" means a distillery that produces more than twenty - five
21 thousand gallons of distilled spirits per year.
22 14.16. "Microbrew pub" means a brewer that brews ten thousand or fewer barrels of beer per
23 year and sells beer produced or manufactured on the premises for consumption on or
24 off the premises or serves beer produced or manufactured on the premises for
25 purposes of sampling the beer.
26 15.17. "Organization" means a domestic or foreign corporation, general partnership, limited
27 partnership, or limited liability company.
28 18. "Satellite location" means an offsite location owned or leased by a manufacturing
29 distillery to conduct retail operations.
30 16.19. "Sparkling wine" means wine made effervescent with carbon dioxide.
