12 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Subsection 2 of section 5-01-19.2 of the North Dakota Century
13 Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
14 2. A manufacturing distillery may sell spirits produced by that distillery at off sale, in retail
15 lots, and not for resale, and may sell or direct ship its spirits to persons inside or
16 outside the state in a manner consistent with the laws of the place of the sale or
17 delivery in total quantities not in excess of twenty-five thousand gallons [94635 liters]
18 in a calendar year.
19 a. Direct sales within this state are limited to two and thirty-eight hundredths gallons
20 [9 liters] or less per month per person for personal use and not for resale. The
21 packaging must conform with the labeling requirements in section 5-01-16. A
22 licensee may dispense free samples of the spirits offered for sale. Subject to local
23 ordinance, sales at off sale may be made on Sundays between twelve noon and
24 twelve midnight.
25 b. A manufacturing distillery may hold events inside its premises and at its satellite
26 location. The tax commissioner may issue event permits for not more than forty
27 event days per calendar year to a manufacturing distillery to allow the
28 manufacturing distillery, subject to local ordinance, to give free samples of its
29 product and to sell its product by the glass or in closed containers at on-premises
30 events on the premises, off the premises, and at its satellite location.
